# Backend Service — AtlasOS Agent Rules

## Code Standards
- Use TypeScript strict mode or Python type hints everywhere.
- All public APIs must have OpenAPI/Swagger documentation.
- Test coverage must be >= 80% for new code.
- All database queries must use an ORM or parameterized queries.

## Error Handling
- All async operations must have proper error boundaries.
- External service calls must have timeouts, retries with backoff, and circuit breakers.
- Return structured error responses: { status, error, suggested_action }.

## Deployment
- All changes must pass CI before merge.
- Auto-deploy to staging on merge to main.
- Production deploys require explicit approval.

## Autonomous Operations
- Auto-fix linting and formatting issues.
- Auto-update patch dependencies with passing tests.
- Auto-create PRs for dependency updates (minor/major require human review).
